'''Ji Xinpeng''' ({{lang-zh|吉新鹏}}, born [[December 30]], [[1977]] in [[Xiamen]], [[Fujian]]) is a retired [[China|Chinese]] [[badminton]] player.

==Career==

Ji Xinpeng is the first Chinese badminton player to win an [[Olympics|Olympic]] gold medal in men's singles. Having never previously captured a top tier event on the international circuit, he surprised the field at the [[Badminton at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Games in Sydney]] by defeating such players as [[Taufik Hidayat]], [[Peter Gade]] and, in the final, [[Hendrawan]]. Ji won men's singles at the [[Japan Open (badminton)|Japan Open]] later that year.

Ji became a coach in the Chinese national badminton team in 2008.
